---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import { links } from '../data/links';
---
<MainLayout title="Writing | Corrine J Blackthorn">
<section>
<div class="container">
<div class="section-heading">
<span class="kicker">Writing</span>
<h1>Writing is how I make sense of the world.</h1>
<p>I write to help people see, understand, question, connect, and feel less alone. Sometimes that takes the form of essays, memoir, technical writing, and sometimes stories.</p>
</div>
<div class="grid">
<article class="card"><h3>All of Me</h3><p>A memoir in progress about identity, survival, resilience, honesty, and becoming whole.</p><a class="button" href={links.ventures.blackthornFieldNotes}>Updates</a></article>
<article class="card"><h3>Blackthorn Field Notes</h3><p>Essays, reflections, technical notes, advocacy writing, observations, and long-form work.</p><a class="button" href={links.ventures.blackthornFieldNotes}>Visit</a></article>
<article class="card"><h3>KDP Publications</h3><p>Current and future books will be listed here as they are published.</p></article>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="quote-band"><div class="container"><blockquote>I write what people need to see and understand.</blockquote></div></section>
<section>
<div class="container">
<div class="section-heading">
<span class="kicker">Current Projects</span>
<h2>What I'm actively working on.</h2>
</div>
<div class="grid">
<article class="card"><h3>All of Me</h3><p>A memoir exploring identity, transition, resilience, trauma, growth, and becoming whole.</p></article>
<article class="card"><h3>Field Notes</h3><p>Personal essays, technology writing, advocacy, observations, and lessons learned.</p></article>
<article class="card"><h3>Future Books</h3><p>Additional nonfiction, technical writing, and creative works planned for publication.</p></article>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section>
<div class="container">
<div class="section-heading">
<span class="kicker">Influences</span>
<h2>Writers who shaped me.</h2>
<p>Chuck Palahniuk, Janet Evanovich, Kevin Mitnick, and Dan Brown each influenced different aspects of how I think about storytelling, pacing, curiosity, and communication.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
</MainLayout>